      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.On2ZrPJTe8FURsXY]{Operative Exploit}</p>\n<p>For your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.bhSrjkuWxz2DQHXC]{debilitating trick}, you can attempt to knock the target @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.XeRGqHVtcZ7vsgJ0]{prone}. The target must succeed at a Reflex save or fall prone. If the target gains a bonus to its KAC against @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.U37n5tY5hn1ctzQL.JournalEntryPage.R33uiOMesYP0ISWl#trip]{trip combat maneuvers}, it adds this bonus to its saving throw, and if it is immune to the trip combat maneuver it is immune to this operative exploit. Once youâ€™ve used this ability to attempt to knock a target prone, that creature is immune to your knee shot for 24 hours. This exploit counts as @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.o2GDNS1g87yquIMS]{Staggering Shot (Ex)} for the purpose of meeting the prerequisites of other operative exploits.</p>"
